## Overview
The OSF Registry of Experiments is a platform for publishing and sharing pre-analysis plans, experimental designs, and other resources related to specific experiments.

## Purpose
The purpose of the OSF Registry of Experiments is to facilitate transparency and collaboration in research by making experimental designs publicly available before data collection begins.

## How it works
Researchers use a pre-analysis plan template to declare their experimental design, which is then uploaded to the OSF or EGAP registry. This allows others to access and build upon existing research plans.

## Requirements
A pre-analysis plan is required to effectively use the OSF Registry of Experiments.

## Reflections
When using the tool for R&D purposes, researchers should consider the importance of transparency and collaboration in ensuring the validity and reliability of their findings.
